Unknown gunmen attacked and burned down the country residence of Imo State Commissioner for Information and Strategy, Chief Declan Emelumba. According to reports, the attack on the house in Oru East Local Government Area occurred about 1 a.m. on Sunday. According to reports, the perpetrators destroyed all of the property in the building before torching it. READ ALSO: Liyel Imoke: What i will do to Ayade if he tries to return to PDP They were claimed to have broken down the house’s gate to gain access and proceeded with their business unchallenged. The incident has been confirmed by Chief Emelumba himslef, The Nation reports. More details later…